# Task: Evaluate DataConcentrator Animation

## Checklist
- [x] Open http://localhost:3001/en and locate the animation.
- [x] Check if Google Ads icons are visible. (Present in DOM but stacked/hidden)
- [x] Inspect the DOM for image paths and loading errors. (Paths are correct, images are loaded)
- [x] Check network and console for script or asset errors. (SVG attribute errors in console)
- [x] Observe animation quality (smoothness, aesthetics). (Low fidelity, simple dots)
- [x] Identify opportunities for "premium" enhancements (glassmorphism, glow, trails).
- [ ] Document findings and recommendations.

## Findings
- **Google Ads Icons**:
    - They are present in the DOM (8 instances) but are all stacked at roughly the same coordinates (`x~940, y~280`), which seems to be the center of the animation.
    - They are not distributed around the periphery as intended.
    - They are wrapped in glassmorphism containers (`backdrop-blur-sm`), but because they are stacked and likely behind the central logo, they are invisible.
- **Console Errors**: 
    - `Error: <circle> attribute cx: Expected length, "undefined"`.
    - This indicates that the Framer Motion animation is failing to pass coordinates to the SVG circle elements. These circles are likely the "data pulses" that should be moving along the lines.
- **Animation Quality**:
    - The current visual state is very basic: static lines and small moving dots (pulses) that are failing to render correctly.
    - It lacks the "premium" feel requested (no glow, no trails, no depth).
    - The "Adecos Data Core" text is just plain text below the central logo.
- **Recommendations for "Premium" feel**:
    - Fix the icon distribution (position them at the ends of the lines).
    - Add `glowing trails` using SVG filters or layered paths.
    - Use `glassmorphism` more effectively on the central core and the peripheral icons.
    - Add a "pulse" effect to the central logo when data hits it.
    - Fix the SVG attribute errors to ensure all visual elements are rendered.
